Diagnosis.
The species is characterized by: 
1
) medium size (SVL 
40.5–53.5 mm
in males and 
34.6
–62.0 mm in females); 
2
) nasal bones broadly separated in their medial region; 
3
) nasal bone broadly separated from frontoparietal in their posterior region; 
4
) small iliac projection (iliac projection representing less than 
30
% of ilium diameter) (

Fig. 
5

F and G); 
5
) frontoparietal bones very depressed and broad rostrally (

Fig. 
5

E); 
6
) nasal and squamosal bones with smooth surface (without or with very reduced swellings and tubercles); 
7
) maxillary pits very reduced, almost vestigial; 
8
) female presenting the gular region dark brown (

Fig. 
8

B).

Geographical distribution. The new species is known from the municipalities of Cunha , São Sebastião, São Luis do Paraitinga, and Ubatuba in São Paulo state, Brazil (
Fig. 7
).
